A data engineer submits this request:

```http
POST /api/2.2/jobs/create
```
```json
{
  "name": "daily-sales-pipeline",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "task_key": "validate_sql",
      "sql_task": {
        "query": { "query_id": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222" }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Why will this request fail validation?

Review this REST API task definition:

```json
{
  "task_key": "run_etl_pipeline",
  "pipeline_task": {
    "pipeline_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
    "full_refresh": false
  }
}
```

What does `"full_refresh": false` control?

A job has four chained tasks: `ingest_notebook` → `run_pipeline` → `validate_sql` → `refresh_dashboard`, each depending on the previous one, as shown in this REST API body:

```json
{
  "task_key": "refresh_dashboard",
  "depends_on": [{ "task_key": "validate_sql" }],
  "dashboard_task": { "dashboard_id": "33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333" }
}
```

If `validate_sql` fails, what happens to `refresh_dashboard` by default?
